judge

public boolean judge(java.lang.String winners,
                     java.lang.String losers)
This method takes string describing which aspects are regarded as winners and losers from an optimisation and returns a judgement as to whether or not that optimisation fits with the specified preference. e.g. winners = "F", losers ="SG" would be interpreted as F is favoured, S and G may be penalised and other aspects are unaffected.

The judgement is in favour if the lowest priority winner is favoured ahead of the highest priority loser.

Parameters:
winners -
losers -
Returns:
true if the optimisation preferences are consistent with these winners and losers.
